description:
Mô Tả Công Việc


              **General

              - Oversee the development and implementation of HR initiatives to support the Company;

              - Guiding and managing the overall provision of HR service, policies & programs;

              - As a proactive HR business partner, maintain strong liaison and working relationship with business department and provide effective solutions on people practices and human resources processes;

              -  Act as an advisor and provide value added solutions to the business in the area of recruitment, compensation & benefits, learning & development, etc…

              - Lead and develop/train HR team as well as ensuring the optimal structure is in place;

              - Formulate and recommend Human Resource policies that keep the Company abreast of current practice and informed of new developments;

              - Directs the preparation and maintenance of reports that are necessary to carry out functions of the department;

              - Protects the interests of both employer and employee in accordance with the company's human resources policies and appropriate governmental laws and regulations;

              - Coordinate with regional head office in HK and other BU HRs for HR projects;

              - Under any circumstances, to give a quality image of her belonging to the DACHSER GROUP Enthusiasm, Professionalism, Straightforwardness;


              *Manpower planning

              - Make manpower planning by organization analysis and ensure optimization of resources in each branch/ department organization structure;

              - Ensure all recruitment needs are fulfilled through effective recruitment channel and process;

              - Work with Management on workforce planning, regarding quality/ quantity/ source of talents;

              - Submit monthly HR reports accurately and timely, including organization chart, contact list, turnover rate, HC report, etc.

              - Make record of leaves management, and report regularly;


              *Compensation & Benefits

              - Implement C&B strategy and program, ensure the internal equity and external competitiveness;

              - Identify the areas for improvement for both office and field force through market intelligence study;

              - Support Management to set up and maintain salary structure and payroll policy & procedure;

              - Ensure timely and accurate monthly payroll/labor cost report, including coordinate with agencies for the payment and social insurances submission;

              - Support Management to participate annual salary survey and submit data;


              *Communication

              - Support Management on handling employee relationships;

              - Provide consultancy/advise to line managers on employee grievances and disciplinary case;

              - Advice line managers in interpretation and application of human resources policies;

              - Implement effective communication plan ensuring all levels of employees goals aligned with business goals;

              - Drive positive employee relations through development and application of policies, practices and programs that drive employee involvement and ownership.


              *Performance Management

              - Facilitate the performance management cycle of each branch office under the corporate guideline;

              - Responsible for the performance training and feedback collection;

              - Update performance schedule and summarize final result to Management;

              - Manage employee file both in hard copies and on HR system to keep performance appraisal, leave record and personal data up to date.


              *Training and Development

              - Support HR Regional and Management work with each office/department to identify the development needs of employees and propose solutions;

              - Ensure that the full spectrum of training and development activities are implemented smoothly;

              - Facilitate regular Talent Review and Succession Planning, and ensure the individual development plans are well implemented;

              - Be responsible for delivering the orientation program for office staff, work closely with each branch office to provide the suggestions on programs and vendors


              *HR Administration

              - Responsible for probation review and labor contract/dispatched contract/outsourced contract renew issues;

              - Keep in complete secrecy all confidential information received in the course of her duty from the Management of the Company or other sources;

              - Under any circumstances, to give a quality image of her belonging to the DACHSER GROUP Enthusiasm, Professionalism, Straightforwardness;

              - Any others additional task and duties required by the Management


              Xem toàn bộ Mô Tả Công Việc

requirement:
Yêu Cầu Công Việc


              - Bachelor or Master Degree holder in Human Resources, business or related field


              *Experience:

              - Minimum 5 years of experience in in HR function area, preferably in multi-national forwarding company;

              - Rich experiences in HR function with at least 3 years overall HR management, preferably in multi-national forwarding industry


              *Language Skills:

              - Fluent English both in written and speaking;


              *Computer Skills:

              - Good Microsoft office operation skill;


              *Core Competencies:

              - Financial results;

              - Teamwork and co-operation skills;

              - Facilitation and management skills;

              - Communication and negotiation skills;

              - Planning and organization skills;

              - Creative problem solving ability;

              - High integrity

              - Excellent planning skills with strategic thinking;

              - Hands-on experience in HR operational activities and detail oriented mindset;

              - Good project management skills;

              - Excellent interpersonal skills with strong adaptability into a dynamic environment;

              - Focus on quality spirit, result oriented.

              - Initiative, mature and open-minded;

              - Able to work under high pressure;

              - High integrity


